# VS Code Configuration Standards

Apply these conventions when creating or modifying VS Code workspace configuration files.

## settings.json

Keep workspace settings minimal — only override defaults that are necessary for the project. Store in `.vscode/settings.json` and commit it.

```json
{
  "editor.formatOnSave": true,
  "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
    "source.fixAll.eslint": "explicit",
    "source.organizeImports": "explicit"
  },
  "files.trimTrailingWhitespace": true,
  "files.insertFinalNewline": true
}
```

## tasks.json

Define tasks for the most common developer operations. Use descriptive labels. Group related tasks with `"group"`:

```json
{
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "tasks": [
    {
      "label": "Build",
      "type": "shell",
      "command": "${workspaceFolder}/scripts/build.sh",
      "group": { "kind": "build", "isDefault": true },
      "presentation": { "reveal": "always", "panel": "shared" },
      "problemMatcher": []
    },
    {
      "label": "Test",
      "type": "shell",
      "command": "${workspaceFolder}/scripts/test.sh",
      "group": { "kind": "test", "isDefault": true },
      "presentation": { "reveal": "always", "panel": "shared" },
      "problemMatcher": []
    }
  ]
}
```

## extensions.json

Only recommend extensions that are essential for working on this project. Avoid bloating the list with personal preferences:

```json
{
  "recommendations": [
    "golang.go",
    "hashicorp.terraform",
    "dbaeumer.vscode-eslint",
    "esbenp.prettier-vscode"
  ]
}
```

## launch.json

Provide debug configurations for the main entry points. Use `${workspaceFolder}` for all paths:

```json
{
  "version": "0.2.0",
  "configurations": [
    {
      "name": "Launch Server",
      "type": "go",
      "request": "launch",
      "mode": "debug",
      "program": "${workspaceFolder}/cmd/server",
      "env": { "ENV": "development" }
    }
  ]
}
```

## mcp.json

VS Code MCP configuration for AI tool integrations. Store at `.vscode/mcp.json`:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "github": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-github"],
      "env": {
        "GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN": "${env:GITHUB_TOKEN}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## What to gitignore

Add `.vscode/settings.local.json` to `.gitignore` for personal overrides that should not be shared. Commit `.vscode/settings.json`, `tasks.json`, `extensions.json`, and `launch.json`.
